President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday paid glowing tributes to his long-time ally and friend, Prof Tamunoemi Sokari David-West, who served as Minister of Petroleum Resources between January 1984 and August 1985. At the commendation service for the former minister held at the Chapel of Resurrection, University of Ibadan, the President said Prof David-West would be sorely missed for his integrity, sense of accountability and radical opposition to corruption. A statement by Mr Attah Esa, the Deputy Director (Information), State House, in Abuja on Wednesday, said President Buhari was represented at the event by Minister of State, Petroleum Resources, Timipre Sylva, and Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina. President Buhari said:  “The late Professor stood for all that was noble and just,” President Buhari said through his Adviser on Media, adding: “He had an indomitable spirit, stood by whatever he believed in, and was very loyal. May his soul Rest In Peace.” Buhari launches national security roadmap APC chides PDP over threat to boycott future election Buhari seeks Senate’s confirmation of National Hajj… UPDATE: Nigeria, Russia sign agreement on potash supply ALSO READ: Minimum wage: Jigawa to commence payment in December The President urged Nigerians to emulate the virtues of the former minister, including his scrupulous commitment to scholarship, timeliness and loyalty to the motherland. Also at the event were the Governor of Edo State, Godwin Obaseki, renowned academics, politicians, family members and admirers of the eminent virologist who attained national and international acclaims. Tam David-West passed away on Nov 11, 2019, aged 83. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
